                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Great Britain/317a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_MAW1" type="to"
                            >Mellon</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 74</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-10">June 10,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding the
                    President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of intergovernmental
                    debts and transmits for the information of the American Ambassador copy of the
                    “Agreement between the Government of the United Kingdom and the United States of
                    America, June 4, 1932”.<note n="54" xml:id="d424fn54">
                        <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the Treasury</hi>, 1932,
                        pp. 296–297.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
